{"id":18308,"date":"2024-01-15T22:28:04","date_gmt":"2021-01-15T16:58:04","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=18308"},"modified":"2023-04-17T15:39:34","modified_gmt":"2023-04-17T10:09:34","slug":"small-dressing-table-ideas","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bedroom-interiors\/small-dressing-table-ideas\/","title":{"rendered":"8 Small Dressing Table Design Ideas For Small Bedrooms"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><em>You can fit a dreamy dressing table in a small bedroom too!<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Every bedroom needs a dressing table! Apart from providing a designated area for getting dressed and ready, your dressing table can provide additional storage for your grooming essentials in the bedroom. If you don\u2019t have a spacious bedroom that can accommodate a big dresser or a designated area for the dressing table, there are many ways in which you can incorporate this essential space even in a small bedroom. Check out these eight small dressing table design ideas for <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bedroom-interiors\/small-bedroom-design-ideas\/\">small bedrooms<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">An Extension Of Your Wardrobe<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Think of it this way \u2014 without a dressing table, all of your grooming and everyday essentials are anyway going to need some storage space, mostly in your wardrobe. While designing the wardrobe, you can leave out just enough space for a small dressing table, complete with a mirror, storage space and a stool. You get exactly what you need without having to scour for corners for leftover space.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221937\/small-dressing-table-attached-to-wardrobe.jpg\" alt=\"White bedroom with small dressing table at corner attached to the wardrobe\" class=\"wp-image-18314\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221937\/small-dressing-table-attached-to-wardrobe.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221937\/small-dressing-table-attached-to-wardrobe-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221937\/small-dressing-table-attached-to-wardrobe-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221937\/small-dressing-table-attached-to-wardrobe-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A dressing table can easily fit into the design structure of your wardrobe<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Utilise That Unused Corner<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Speaking of leftover space, there are usually similar corners even in small bedrooms where you won\u2019t be able to fit a large piece of furniture. You can utilise such leftover corners to install a petite dressing table unit, complete with drawers and a full-length mirror.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221913\/corner-small-dressing-table-with-mirror.jpg\" alt=\"Small dressing table with a mirror at a spare corner in the bedroom looks chic\" class=\"wp-image-18310\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221913\/corner-small-dressing-table-with-mirror.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221913\/corner-small-dressing-table-with-mirror-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221913\/corner-small-dressing-table-with-mirror-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221913\/corner-small-dressing-table-with-mirror-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A spare corner in your bedroom can easily accommodate a small dressing table<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Get a Free Modular Kitchen Worth \u20b92 Lakhs with Your Home Interiors.\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/08183703\/designcafe-offer-free-modular-kitchen-worth-2-lakhs.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Floating Drawers For A Small Dressing Table<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A great hack for adding a small dressing table unit to a small bedroom is by keeping the unit off the floor. Floating drawers can be easily added to a spare corner of your small bedroom. Along with a mirror and some cute decor, you can make way for a dressing table in no time.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221948\/small-size-dressing-table-with-floating-drawers.jpg\" alt=\"Floating small size dressing table with wardrobe attached in the bedroom looks modern\" class=\"wp-image-18316\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221948\/small-size-dressing-table-with-floating-drawers.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221948\/small-size-dressing-table-with-floating-drawers-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221948\/small-size-dressing-table-with-floating-drawers-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221948\/small-size-dressing-table-with-floating-drawers-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A floating dressing table unit frees up ground space<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Vertical Dressing Unit<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The problem with a small bedroom is that there is too much to accommodate within a small space. You can easily avoid cluttering the floor of a small bedroom by adding a mirror and a vertical dressing unit. This way, not only do you get your small dressing unit and storage space, but it also maximises the available space in a small bedroom by staying off the floor.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221953\/vertical-dressing-table-idea-for-small-bedroom.jpg\" alt=\"Wall hanged vertical dressing table design for small bedroom with clutter-free storage space\" class=\"wp-image-18317\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221953\/vertical-dressing-table-idea-for-small-bedroom.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221953\/vertical-dressing-table-idea-for-small-bedroom-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221953\/vertical-dressing-table-idea-for-small-bedroom-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221953\/vertical-dressing-table-idea-for-small-bedroom-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Save up on space on the floor with a unit that takes up vertical space<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Portable Dressing Unit<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Fitted furniture might not always fare well in a small space. With such constraints, it is always better to have furniture that can be moved around as and when required. A portable full-length mirror and a matching sleek table are a great alternative to small dressing tables. The mirror can also be propped directly against the wall to save on more space.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221931\/portable-dressing-table-design-for-small-bedroom.jpg\" alt=\"Portable white dressing unit and full-length mirror with a sleek look are a dressing table idea for small bedroom\" class=\"wp-image-18313\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221931\/portable-dressing-table-design-for-small-bedroom.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221931\/portable-dressing-table-design-for-small-bedroom-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221931\/portable-dressing-table-design-for-small-bedroom-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221931\/portable-dressing-table-design-for-small-bedroom-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A portable mirror and table can be fitted into any corner of your bedroom and moved around too if needed<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Fully Utilise Your Wall Space<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The best thing about dressing tables is that they don\u2019t need to be in a specific spot in the bedroom. You can have a dressing table beside your wardrobe, or one near the door or window \u2014 practically any corner of the room. You can think of keeping a small section for the dressing table next to your wardrobe where you can have all your bedroom storage options on one side of the room.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221959\/wardrobe-design-for-small-bedroom-with-dressing-table.jpg\" alt=\"Dressing unit with mirror and drawers in the small bedroom attached to the wardrobe\" class=\"wp-image-18318\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221959\/wardrobe-design-for-small-bedroom-with-dressing-table.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221959\/wardrobe-design-for-small-bedroom-with-dressing-table-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221959\/wardrobe-design-for-small-bedroom-with-dressing-table-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221959\/wardrobe-design-for-small-bedroom-with-dressing-table-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>With small spaces, you must smartly utilise every corner<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Go For Half A Dressing Table<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A small bedroom calls for a small dressing table. If you want to cut down on the space you will end up utilising with a full-size dressing table, you can always consider going for smaller alternatives. This dressing table occupies a smaller area due to its design. You can easily prop a mirror and store your daily beauty essentials on the surface. A pouffe or a stool can be stowed away under the table when not in use, or pretty much anywhere else in the room.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221919\/half-dressing-table-for-small-room.jpg\" alt=\"Moveable semi-circular wooden dressing table for small room looks minimalist and modern\" class=\"wp-image-18311\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221919\/half-dressing-table-for-small-room.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221919\/half-dressing-table-for-small-room-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221919\/half-dressing-table-for-small-room-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221919\/half-dressing-table-for-small-room-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A table with a semi-circular surface takes up only half of the usual space required<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Want a dressing room that makes yoru feel gorgeous every day\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/09111527\/want-a-dressing-room-that-makes-yoru-feel-gorgeous-every-day.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Multipurpose Small Dressing Table<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The all-grey dressing table is among the exceptional modern dressing table designs for small bedroom. For a small bedroom, you can add a multipurpose dressing table that can act as an additional surface or storage space. You can prop a mirror on the top and add a stool with dimensions that allow it to fit under the small dressing table itself.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221925\/multipurpose-modern-small-dressing-table.jpg\" alt=\"All-grey modern small dressing table with drawers in the bedroom look adored\" class=\"wp-image-18312\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221925\/multipurpose-modern-small-dressing-table.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221925\/multipurpose-modern-small-dressing-table-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221925\/multipurpose-modern-small-dressing-table-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/15221925\/multipurpose-modern-small-dressing-table-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>This small dressing table is almost like an extension of the bed<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Based on your need and use of the dressing table, you can make way for a small unit in a small bedroom in a hassle-free way. We suggest you keep the small dressing table design minimal and movable for your comfort.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Explore, More About<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/dressing-table-design\/\">Dressing Table Design<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-decor\/dressing-table-decor-ideas\/\">Dressing Table Decor Ideas<\/a><\/li><\/ul>\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row blog-form\">\n\t<div class=\"offset-lg-3 col-lg-6 bg-light\">\n<fieldset class=\"field-set\">\n<!-- <legend align=\"left\"> -->\n                    \n    <h3 class=\"widget-title text-dark text-center mb-0\">Unwind In Your Personal Sanctuary<\/h3>\n  \n \n     <p class=\"text-center text-dark mt-0\"> Get 20% extra space with modular interiors<\/p>\n    <!-- <\/legend> -->\n<form id=\"blogContactUsFormMain\" action=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/get_quote_action.php\" method=\"post\"\n    novalidate=\"novalidate\">\n    <div class=\"form-group\">\n        <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\"  name=\"your-name\" placeholder=\"Enter your name*\" \/>\n        <!-- <span class=\"sales-txt-label\" id=\"labeltxt\">Enter your name*<\/span>  -->\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"form-row dc-falg-row\">\n        <!-- <div class=\"form-group col-md-3 guideForm\">\n            <select name=\"your-phone-ext\" id=\"id_select2_example\" class=\"id_select2_example drop-downfield form-dropdown\"\n                onfocus='this.size=5;' onblur='this.size=1;' onchange='this.size=1; this.blur();'\n                data-width=\"100%\" data-minimum-results-for-search=\"Infinity\">\n               \n                <option value=\"+01\"\n                    data-img_src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/06163948\/01.png\">\n                    +01\n                <\/option>\n                <option value=\"+91\"\n                    data-img_src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/06164015\/91.png\"\n                    selected>